each item in `iterable`. `fn` can return either a Promise or Observable. If `fn`

to `fn` may not. (so avoid side effects)

functions.label: modifyUrl
description:
Takes a URL and a function that takes the meaningful parts
 of the URL as a key-value object, modifies some or all of
 the parts, and returns the modified parts formatted again
 as a url.

 Url Parts sent:
   - protocol
   - slashes (does the url have the //)
   - auth
   - hostname (just the name of the host, no port or auth information)
   - port
   - pathname (the path after the hostname, no query or hash, starts
       with a slash if there was a path)
   - query (always an object, even when no query on original url)
   - hash

 Why?
   - The default url library in node produces several conflicting
     properties on the "parsed" output. Modifying any of these might
     lead to the modifications being ignored (depending on which
     property was modified)
   - It's not always clear whether to use path/pathname, host/hostname,
     so this tries to add helpful constraints

functions.label: safeJsonParse
description:
Safely parses a JSON string. If the string cannot be parsed, for instance
if it is not valid JSON, it will return `undefined`. If `handleError` is
defined, it will be called with the error, and the response from the callback
will be returned. This allows consumers to wrap the JSON.parse error.

children.label: value
description: The JSON string to parse.

children.label: handleError
description:
Optional callback that is called when an error
during parsing. Its return value is returned from the
function.

returnComment: The parsed object, or `undefined` if an error occurs.

functions.label: safeJsonStringify
description:
Safely stringifies a value to JSON. If the value cannot be stringified,
for instance if it contains circular references, it will return `undefined`.
If `handleError` is defined, it will be called with the error, and the
response will be returned. This allows consumers to wrap the JSON.stringify
error.
signature: (value: unknown, handleError: (error: Error) => string | undefined) => string | undefined

children.label: value
description: The value to stringify.

children.label: handleError
description:
Optional callback that is called when an error occurs during
stringifying.

returnComment:
The JSON string representation of the value, or `undefined`
if an error occurs.

misc.label: FromExternalVariant
